The entrance to this lost sector is found firstly through the ceiling of this tiny volcano, secondly keep left and, ...
Guarded by a Vex Harpy, this object lies in the corner of a large space before you turn left and pass through a warp gate.
In a tight corner of a large space where three plates must be captured in order to push forward and onwards through another warp gate.

After passing through the final warp gate, you find yourself on a large ramp. Before facing _The Genesis Mind_, make a hard right at the bottom of the ramp. Climb a small sand beach and head into the shadow of the construct.
To the right, just off of the strike's beat and path, under a ramp.
On the ceiling of a platform that extends above some large ammunition.
Top rear corner of this garage.
An item lays on the front seat of a rusty truck.
A Fallen house banner hangs between two buildings.
On the uppermost level of a damaged building, in the darkest corner, is a small green toolbox.
One of the minor rooms along the tunnels servers as an access way to an auxiliary area. Search the farthest corner.
Use the wall, as pictured, to climb above this particle beam.

Enter the wall and follow the path for a time. You'll reach a stream of radiolaria. Heading forwards and upwards, you'll notice rays of light shining from behind some boulders on your right. Investigate them and find a small opening at the source of the light. Follow the light to the artifact.
After completing the sector, proceed to the exit and find the subject on the way out.
Requires a Firewall Data Fragment. Acquire prerequisite through Eris Morn.

Entering the Circle of Bones via The Gatehouse, turn right and proceed to follow the loop around the Hellmouth. Before reaching the next junction, turn on your heel and look beneath the platform to find two jade eyes piercing through your Traveler-given light.
In one of the corners of the uppermost floor of this construction is a barely open cupboard along the wall. Look inside.

On the farthest side of the largest room, adjacent to the lost sector's chest room, is a large rock wall which has a path leading around into a small poorly lit room with a computer desk. On this desk is a defunct ghost.
Right before the lost sector's primary space, on your left.
Outside the lost sector's chest room is a series of metal walking platforms. Beneath these platforms lay a small maze, at the end of which is a data cache.

A hard cache to find, this enigma is hidden at the end of a cave which has a small opening along the wall not far from the lost sector's chest. If you're having difficulty locating its orifice, increase your brightness in settings.
Enter the dungeon and head to the tower farthest right. Retain some altitude if possible. On the farthest side of the farthest tower, below its foot, is a cypher.

Complete the Necropolis encounter and proceed towards The Pit. Once at the wall of paths, climb and turn around. To the right of the hall is a small ledge along the moonstone wall. Use it to step to the upper level of the hallway and proceed to the farthest right side.
Complete the Tunnels of Despair encounter. Before making your way deeper by traversing the height traps, climb carefully to their higest level.

Drop down into the Tunnels of Despair and keep right. Enter at the first crouch-way and follow it to its end. You'll see a red door. Standing at the red door turn 70Â° clockwise. You'll be staring at a boulder. To the right of the boulder is the prize you seek.

In the middlest crouch-way tunnel, closest to the green gas pit where you find the solar orb. Entering the tunnel from the green gas pit side, it will quickly widen into a small room. Stop, turn 180Â°, and look upwards.
Enter the The Gatehouse via the HellMouth and follow it to a well-lit circular room. Along the windowed-wall on the right is what you seek.
At the side on the hidden side of the pictured module.
In the Tunnels of Despair, on a cliff ledge adjacent to the green gas pit.
On the lowest of ice shelves, beneath a fallen Warsat.
To the right of the elevator.
